snippet: Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Representative Paul D. Ryan held their positions tenaciously and delineated battle lines that had been blurred when President Obama and Mitt Romney met a week ago.
abstract: News analysis; Vice President Joseph R Biden Jr and Rep Paul D Ryan, in lively and sometimes fiery vice-presidential debate, hold their positions tenaciously and delineate battle lines that had been blurred when President Obama and Mitt Romney met in the previous week; how much change American voters are ready for may determine whom they side with in days to come.
lead_paragraph: Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Representative Paul D. Ryan held their positions tenaciously and delineated battle lines that had been blurred when President Obama and Mitt Romney met a week ago.

headline.seo: Biden vs. Ryan: No Shy People Onstage
headline.main: Biden vs. Ryan: No Shy People Onstage
